cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper presents a practical and statistically consistent scheme for actively learning binary classifiers, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of importance weighting to correct sampling bias is a key aspect of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on passively labeled data, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of binary classifiers also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
